			<div class="content" id="post-content-3803382">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Previous&nbsp;crit</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">go&nbsp;away</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I have no issue with the subject, but the writing is a bit dodgy.</p>
<p>I was distracted by some of the word choice, and overall &quot;loose&quot; feeling among the action descriptions.</p>
<p>I'm giving it a -1 for the writing, which should be touched up a bit; I'm always pro-silly-stuff on the wiki though. Clean up the last section:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As Doctor Omel began reaching towards 049, the small plague doctor in its arms spun around and smacked his hand with a stick out of nowhere.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>It was small, and looked kind of funny in comparison to its father. SCP-049 let out a gasp of excitement and picked up the small doctor, hugging it in its arms.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>A preponderance of the actual sentences and actions start with &quot;as&quot; or are passive.</p>
<p>Tighten up the writing, and I'd upvote.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Issues were addressed. -1 ==&gt; +1</p>

							</div>

								
